post_text: Join City of Phoenix Vice Mayor and Councilwoman Betty Guardado for an online presentation on an opportunity to create a Food Innovation Center in the former K-Mart building on I-17 and Northern. This project will help to revitalize the community by providing long-term career opportunities for children as they progress from elementary school, to high school, to career training at college level and beyond. To share your input and ideas, tune in to the virtual meeting on Thursday, June 25 from 5:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m. To RSVP and receive the link or phone number for the meeting, please send your name, email address and phone number to phx.business@phoenix.gov or call 602-262-5040. Thank you.

Please join us in congratulating Sunnyslope senior Alexis Hatch! She is officially a recipient of the prestigious National Merit $2,500 Scholarship! The $2,500 Merit Scholar designees were chosen from a talent pool of more than 15,000 finalists in the 2020 National Merit
Scholarship Program. Recipients were selected in each state that had the strongest combination of accomplishments, skills, and potential for success in rigorous college studies. Way to go, Alexis! #ExcellenceContinues #SunnyslopeProud #WeAreGUHSD

post_text: Amazing job to Sunnyslope Teacher and Librarian Patty Jimenez who created the QuaranTeens Read Program to keep her students engaged during remote learning. Read more about the program below. #ExcellenceContinues #SunnyslopeProud #WeAreGUHSD
shared_text:
Sunnyslope High School
April 30 at 1:49 PM ·

To celebrate readers and encourage them to keep reading, Sunnyslope Teacher and Librarian Patty Jimenez created the SHS QuaranTeens Read Program. It is a way for students and staff to share what they have been reading and to win new books. Each week, 10 names are drawn from those who shared what they read. Each winner receives two new books, one to keep and one to give to a friend. All prizes will be distributed when school resumes on campus. During the program's first week, participants submitted more than 80 books which were added to the virtual bulletin board. SHS QuaranTeens Read will continue through July 31, 2020. #ExcellenceContinues #SunnyslopeProud #WeAreGUHSD

post_text: Glendale Choir students have been actively participating in a virtual version of choir over the past four weeks during remote learning. post_text: We're proud to announce that Washington senior Priscilla Villalobos Ixcotoyac is officially a recipient of the prestigious Flinn Scholarship! The scholarship is valued at more than $120,000 and can be used at any in-state university. Other benefits of the Flinn Scholarship include funding for one study-abroad experience, personal mentoring from top faculty and much more. Amazing job, Priscilla! #ExcellenceContinues #WashingtonProud #WeAreGUHSD

April 16 at 3:21 PM ·

Congratulations to the following students who will be representing the state of Arizona and competing online in the National Speech and Debate Tournament! The lucky students include: Sophomore Emma Claus (2nd Qualifier in Congressional Debate- House), Junior Dylan Lifshitz (2nd Qualifier in Congressional Debate- Senate), Sophomore Ezri Tyler (3rd Qualifier in Original Oratory Speech) and Senior Alexis Hatch (1st Qualifier in Informational Speech). Reminder: USDA guidelines allows us to serve meals during “unscheduled” closings and therefore we will serve grab-and-go meals available from March 23-April 10, Monday-Friday, 9-11 a.m.

• Free meals will be served to any child 18 and younger
• No paperwork required
• Children must be present
• Meals include breakfast & lunch (given out at the same time)

Meals will be provided at Apollo, Cortez, Glendale, Greenway, Independence, Moon Valley, Sunnyslope, Thunderbird, and Washington high schools between 9-11 a.m.

School closure updates will be available at the following websites:
www.guhsdaz.org
https://www.facebook.com/GUHSDAZ/
www.twitter.com/GlendaleUnionAZ

post_text:
Congratulations to the Sunnyslope German students on this achievement!

#SunnyslopeProud #WeAreGUHSD
shared_text:
Sunnyslope High School
February 24 at 10:56 AM ·

Congratulations to SHS German students who won first place in the category of Advanced Known Play at Friday's Language Fair. They performed a modern version of Chicken Little/Henny Penny as a puppet show. Students hand made puppets over the course of two weeks.

Rose Wiesinger also received a first-place certificate as she played the guitar and sang a folk song completely in German.

Other students won for posters they created from Grimm's fairy tales.
1st place: Penelope Kieborz and Yasmina Lubovac
2nd place: Haylee Fuentes and Ivonne Martinez
3rd place: Sarah Epstien
Honorable Mention: Ciarra Garland
#SunnyslopeProud #WeAreGUHSD

post_text: Great job to Glendale National Honor Society! The group recently volunteered with the City of Glendale at Sahuaro Ranch Park to gather grapefruit for St. Mary's Food Bank. #GlendaleProud #WeAreGUHSD
shared_text:
Glendale High School
February 19 at 8:35 AM ·

On February 15, NHS joined other City of Glendale volunteers at Sahuaro Ranch Park to glean grapefruit for St. Mary’s Food Bank. Some of the fruit is also traded with other states (like Idaho for potatoes) to add variety to food bank boxes. Along with other volunteers, we gleaned about 10,000 lbs of fruit!
#WeAreGUHSD #GlendaleProud

post_text: Apollo Teacher Rudy Aguilar, Independence Teacher Matt Massic and Sunnyslope Teacher Tyler Bolen recently attended the 3DEXPERIENCE World Tour 2020 Conference in Nashville. Together, the engineering teachers built a bicycle for the boys and girls club of America with the help of sponsor TRIMECH. They also participated in The Helping Hand Project, where participants help build prosthetic hands which are donated to amputee victims. Amazing job! #WeAreGUHSD
